A grizzled gray wolf with battle scars standing proudly on an oriental rug in a dimly lit Victorian study, facing off against a sleek young fox across the room, both animals in tense but respectful stances, antique bookshelves and leather furniture in the background, warm amber lamplight casting dramatic shadows, dust motes floating in the air, the atmosphere suggesting a long-standing rivalry between worthy opponents, vintage oil painting style with rich textures and muted earth tones reminiscent of classical animal portraiture from the 1800s
